primary

Class WifiReceiver

  • java.lang.Object
    • primary.WifiReceiver

  • public class WifiReceiver
extends java.lang.Object
    Connects to wi-fi. Once the connection has been established, fetch needed parameters from another computer used as a server connected to the same wi-fi. These parameters are then passed to the Initialization class. The ip address of the other computer that is used as a server is saved in this class and might need to be updated.
    Author:
    Charles-William
